      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-forge-orange uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Layer 2</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
        <a href="#build-signing" class="hover:text-forge-orange transition-colors">Build Signing &amp; Integrity</a>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-8 max-w-3xl">
        Forge supports Ed25519 signing of build artifacts for supply chain integrity verification.
      </p>

      <!-- Signing flow -->
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-4">Signing Flow</h3>
      <div class="space-y-3 mb-10 max-w-3xl">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-dark-surface border border-dark-border flex items-center justify-center text-forge-orange font-mono text-xs">1</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm pt-1"><code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">forge build</code> computes SHA-256 checksums of all generated artifacts</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-dark-surface border border-dark-border flex items-center justify-center text-forge-orange font-mono text-xs">2</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm pt-1">If a signing key exists at <code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">~/.forge/signing-key.pem</code>, checksums are signed with Ed25519</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-dark-surface border border-dark-border flex items-center justify-center text-forge-orange font-mono text-xs">3</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm pt-1"><code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">checksums.json</code> is written with checksums, signature, and key ID</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Verification flow -->
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-4">Verification Flow</h3>
      <div class="space-y-3 mb-10 max-w-3xl">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-dark-surface border border-dark-border flex items-center justify-center text-forge-orange font-mono text-xs">1</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm pt-1">Validates SHA-256 checksums of all files against <code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">checksums.json</code></p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-dark-surface border border-dark-border flex items-center justify-center text-forge-orange font-mono text-xs">2</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm pt-1">Verifies the Ed25519 signature against trusted keys in <code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">~/.forge/trusted-keys/</code></p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-dark-surface border border-dark-border flex items-center justify-center text-forge-orange font-mono text-xs">3</div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm pt-1">If <code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">checksums.json</code> doesn't exist, verification is skipped (opt-in model)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Key management -->
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-4">Key Management</h3>
      <div class="bg-dark-surface border border-dark-border rounded-forge-md p-4 font-mono text-sm text-gray-300 overflow-x-auto mb-10 max-w-3xl">
        <pre><code>forge key generate                     <span class="text-gray-500"># Generate Ed25519 keypair</span>
forge key generate --name ci-key       <span class="text-gray-500"># Named keypair</span>
forge key trust ~/.forge/signing-key.pub   <span class="text-gray-500"># Add to trusted keyring</span>
forge key list                         <span class="text-gray-500"># List signing + trusted keys</span></code></pre>
      </div>

      <!-- Production build safety -->
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-4">Production Build Safety</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4 max-w-3xl">
        The build pipeline includes a <code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">secret-safety</code> stage that enforces production constraints:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-400 text-sm max-w-3xl">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-forge-orange mt-1 shrink-0">&bull;</span>
          <span>Blocks production builds that only use <code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">encrypted-file</code> without <code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">env</code> provider</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-forge-orange mt-1 shrink-0">&bull;</span>
          <span>Warns if <code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">.dockerignore</code> is missing alongside a generated Dockerfile</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-forge-orange mt-1 shrink-0">&bull;</span>
          <span>Rejects <code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">dev-open</code> egress mode in production builds</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-forge-orange mt-1 shrink-0">&bull;</span>
          <span>Filters out dev-only tools (<code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">local_shell</code>, <code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">local_file_browser</code>)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── J. Guardrails ─── -->
  <section id="guardrails" class="py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-forge-orange uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Layer 1</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
        <a href="#guardrails" class="hover:text-forge-orange transition-colors">Guardrails</a>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-8 max-w-3xl">
        The guardrail engine checks inbound and outbound messages against configurable policy rules.
      </p>

      <!-- Built-in guardrails -->
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-4">Built-in Guardrails</h3>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-10 max-w-4xl">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-dark-border rounded-forge-md overflow-hidden">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-dark-surface">
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-gray-400 font-medium border-b border-dark-border">Guardrail</th>
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-gray-400 font-medium border-b border-dark-border">Direction</th>
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-gray-400 font-medium border-b border-dark-border">Description</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-dark-border">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-mono text-xs">content_filter</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Inbound + Outbound</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Blocks messages containing configured blocked words</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-dark-border bg-dark-surface/50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-mono text-xs">no_pii</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Outbound</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Detects email addresses, phone numbers, and SSNs via regex</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-mono text-xs">jailbreak_protection</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Inbound</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Detects common jailbreak phrases ("ignore previous instructions", etc.)</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Modes -->
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-4">Enforcement Modes</h3>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-10 max-w-3xl">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-dark-border rounded-forge-md overflow-hidden">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-dark-surface">
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-gray-400 font-medium border-b border-dark-border">Mode</th>
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-gray-400 font-medium border-b border-dark-border">Behavior</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-dark-border">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-mono text-xs">enforce</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Blocks violating messages, returns error to caller</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-mono text-xs">warn</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Logs violation, allows message to pass</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Runtime -->
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-4">Runtime</h3>
      <div class="bg-dark-surface border border-dark-border rounded-forge-md p-4 font-mono text-sm text-gray-300 overflow-x-auto max-w-3xl">
        <pre><code><span class="text-gray-500"># Run with guardrails enforced</span>
forge run --enforce-guardrails

<span class="text-gray-500"># Default: warn mode (log only)</span>
forge run</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── K. Audit Logging ─── -->
  <section id="audit-logging" class="py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-forge-orange uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Observability</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
        <a href="#audit-logging" class="hover:text-forge-orange transition-colors">Audit Logging</a>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-8 max-w-3xl">
        All runtime security events are emitted as structured NDJSON to stderr with correlation IDs for end-to-end tracing.
      </p>

      <!-- Event types -->
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-4">Event Types</h3>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-10 max-w-4xl">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-dark-border rounded-forge-md overflow-hidden">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-dark-surface">
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-gray-400 font-medium border-b border-dark-border">Event</th>
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-gray-400 font-medium border-b border-dark-border">Description</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-dark-border">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-mono text-xs">session_start</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">New task session begins</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-dark-border bg-dark-surface/50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-mono text-xs">session_end</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Task session completes (with final state)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-dark-border">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-mono text-xs">tool_exec</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Tool execution start/end (with tool name)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-dark-border bg-dark-surface/50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-mono text-xs">egress_allowed</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Outbound request allowed (with domain, mode)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-dark-border">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-mono text-xs">egress_blocked</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Outbound request blocked (with domain, mode)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-dark-border bg-dark-surface/50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-mono text-xs">llm_call</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">LLM API call completed (with token count)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-mono text-xs">guardrail_check</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-300">Guardrail evaluation result</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Correlation threading -->
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-4">Correlation Threading</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6 max-w-3xl">
        Every event carries a 16-hex-character <code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">correlation_id</code> that links all events within a single task session. The <code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">source</code> field distinguishes in-process enforcer events from subprocess proxy events (<code class="text-forge-orange text-xs">"source": "proxy"</code>).
      </p>

      <!-- NDJSON example -->
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-4">Example Output</h3>
      <div class="bg-dark-surface border border-dark-border rounded-forge-md p-4 font-mono text-xs sm:text-sm text-gray-300 overflow-x-auto max-w-4xl">
        <pre><code set:text={ndjsonExample} /></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

